        "annotations": {
          "note": "Dilute primary antibodies in blocking solution (Table 3 or manufacturer’s instructions). Nuclear staining in human organoids is challenging; most retinal antibodies are nuclear transcription factors. Perform heat-induced antigen retrieval with sodium citrate buffer (10 mM sodium citrate, pH 6) and a microwave. Phalloidin staining requires 1 hour of incubation at RT and light protection. No secondary antibody staining is necessary since phalloidin is conjugated with TRITC."
